{"type":"message-part","messageId":"3f7b5a2b-a314-4f8a-9869-ecf5cb215558","role":"user","index":0,"part":{"type":"text","text":"# Edit Commit Message in Jujutsu\n\n## Background\n\nJujutsu (`jj`) is a modern VCS that makes it easy to modify the history of a repository. It allows editing the commit message (description) of any commit in the history without checking it out, and automatically rebases descendants.\n\n## Requirements\n\n* Find the commit with the description \"Add file B\" in the repository history.\n* Change its description to \"Add second file\".\n* Create a new commit on top of the current working copy with the description \"Add file D\" and add a new file `d.txt` containing the text \"d\".\n\n## Implementation\n\n1. `cd /home/user/repo`\n2. Use `jj log` or revsets to find the revision of the commit with description \"Add file B\".\n3. Use `jj describe -m \"Add second file\" <revision>` to change its description.\n4. Use `jj new -m \"Add file D\"` to create a new commit on top of the working copy.\n5. Create a file `d.txt` with content \"d\".\n\n## Constraints\n\n* Project path: /home/user/repo"}}
{"type":"message-part","messageId":"3f7b5a2b-a314-4f8a-9869-ecf5cb215558","role":"user","index":0,"part":{"type":"text","text":"<system-reminder># System Information\n\nOperating System: linux\nDefault Shell: \nHome Directory: /root\nCurrent Working Directory: /\nCurrent Time: Wed Apr 15 2026 02:31:10 GMT+0000 (Coordinated Universal Time)\n\n# GIT STATUS\nCurrent branch: \nMain branch (you will usually use this for PRs): \n\nRecent commits:\n\n\n# TODOs\nNo TODOs yet, if you are working on tasks that would benefit from a todo list please use the todoWrite tool to create one.</system-reminder>"}}
{"type":"message-part","messageId":"3f7b5a2b-a314-4f8a-9869-ecf5cb215558","role":"user","index":1,"part":{"type":"text","text":"# Edit Commit Message in Jujutsu\n\n## Background\n\nJujutsu (`jj`) is a modern VCS that makes it easy to modify the history of a repository. It allows editing the commit message (description) of any commit in the history without checking it out, and automatically rebases descendants.\n\n## Requirements\n\n* Find the commit with the description \"Add file B\" in the repository history.\n* Change its description to \"Add second file\".\n* Create a new commit on top of the current working copy with the description \"Add file D\" and add a new file `d.txt` containing the text \"d\".\n\n## Implementation\n\n1. `cd /home/user/repo`\n2. Use `jj log` or revsets to find the revision of the commit with description \"Add file B\".\n3. Use `jj describe -m \"Add second file\" <revision>` to change its description.\n4. Use `jj new -m \"Add file D\"` to create a new commit on top of the working copy.\n5. Create a file `d.txt` with content \"d\".\n\n## Constraints\n\n* Project path: /home/user/repo"}}
